                                     Churn by Payment Method

                        BUSINESS QUESTION
Which payment method has the highest churn rate?

                     QUERY
SELECT
Payment_Method,
COUNT(*) number_of_customers,
SUM(CASE WHEN Customer_Status = 'Churned' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) Churned_customers,
ROUND(
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Customer_Status = 'Churned' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)AS FLOAT) * 100/COUNT(*),2)Churn_rate
FROM telecom_customer
GROUP  BY Payment_method
ORDER BY ROUND(
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Customer_Status = 'Churned' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)AS FLOAT) * 100/COUNT(*),2) ASC


                             KEY FINDINGS
Mailed Check shows the highest churn rate, indicating that customers using this payment method are more likely to leave,while the
Bank Withdrawal has the highest number of churned customers due to its large customer base 

                          RECOMMENDATION
Our Teams should find out  the reasons behind the high churn rate among Mailed Check users, as this group shows a higher likelihood of leaving. 
At the same time, customers retention strategies should be applied to Bank Withdrawal customers due to their large volume and overall impact on churn.
